Text.Value: I'll be - a fresh face!
I need to lay off the hooch. The manip finds out, she'll kick me clear to Neverwinter.
(...Old Man Otto... back here again... cell stinks like an old cabbage... three bowls of the stew...)

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Talking in her sleep, eyes closed

Text.Value: I'm here to see Old Man Otto. He's my father.
Second cell on the right. And you tell him no seconds for supper. This here's a prison, not an inn.
Er - what now? Goodness, how embarrassing. I had a... heavy lunch.
Hang on, I'll - Aw, what the hells?
The toymaker? Sorry - no can do. High-risk prisoner, no guests allowed.
Listen closely to the guard's babbling.
*The guard is fast asleep.*
You let me through, and I won't tell the manip of your lunchtime tipples.
Leave.
No crazing or criming down there. We run a tight ship.
Prison inspection. Open the door and pray I don't find more sleeping guards.
Last cell on the left. And give that traitor a what-for. She'll know what for.
Hang on. I'll let you through.
I don't have business here. I'm just exploring.
Ah, well - that was a, erm, most unusual, um, circumstances being what they are... ahem.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hemming and hawing trying to make excuses and coming up short.

Text.Value: Excuse me.
Read the guard's mind.
Who takes a damn key? Dirty thieves, that's who.
*You find no meaning in her mutterings.*
Leave.

EditorData.stateContext: Guard is sleeping on a stool

Text.Value: Someone's turned the door to splinters. Just like my bones if the manip hears of this.
Then explore your way out of my personal space. No business, no entry.
Duke Ravengard has sent me to interrogate Florrick.
But I appreciate the effort.
I'm here for Arfur. It's time he answered my questions.
Double hells - I'm the next shift!
Back, eh? What's your business?
Welcome to Wyrm's Rock Prison - the Fist nail, we jail. What's your business?
Aren't you the bloke who exposed the bloody bastard? Access gods-damned granted.
Aren't you the one who exposed the bloody bastard? Access godsdamned granted.
The traitor? No visitors - Ravengard's orders. You understand.
No one out, no one in. Well, some in. But not you.
Your father? Hmph. Not much of a family resemblance. Well -
(...bathed in a tenday... ate all the onions...)

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Talking in her sleep, eyes closed

Text.Value: Damn key's taken a walk. Looks like no one's getting in. Not 'til the next shift.
You're playing with my head? I won't stand for it!
Inspection? Not had one of those for nigh on a decade. I should know - I'm the inspector.
Well. Who am I to argue?
